         <notesStmt>
            
            <note rend="IDENTIFICATION">
               
               <p>Français 1179, Bibliothéque national de France, Paris. Paris, c. 1405-1406. </p>
            
            </note>
            
            <note rend="BASIC INFORMATION">
               
               <p>Parchment, 308 x 214 mm, 134 folios.</p>
            
            </note>
            
            <note rend="MATERIAL">
               
               <p> The <material>parchment</material>, rather yellowed, has many imperfections like some holes and edges, with several holes to the first and last folios, and especially many stitches whose thread is often intact. The <hi rend="italics">vis-à-vis</hi> rule is respected throughout the manuscript.</p>
                  
            </note>
            
